5877 Rust Street (old Flushing Avenue), east side, about 200 feet south of Grand Avenue, showing Froelichs House and milk dairy farm for almost 50 years. Niles Brothers; truckmen, occupied
it in 1923.
March 1923.
Eugene L. Armbruster Collection.
